JOHANNESBURG - The South African music scene is vibrant and diverse, more especially our female jazz musicians. In recent years we've seen them move from the underground scene to the forefront. They're changing the narrative and taking their place in the mainstream scene. One of those strong players is Thandi Ntuli -- a pianist, composer, producer and singer. She was recently acknowledged by the National Arts Festival when she became the recipient of the Standard Bank Young Artist Awards. Ntuli will also be at the Cape Town Jazz Festival later this month where she will be the musical directing for a musical piece with jazz legend Simphiwe Dana and an all-female band. * Watch the full interview in the gallery above. eNCA